                <p dir=3D"ltr"><span>Boolean Algebra is a branch of mathema=
tics that deals with variables that have only two possible values =E2=80=94=
 typically denoted as 0 and 1 (or </span><i><em class=3D"GFGEditorTheme__te=
xtItalic">false</em></i><span> and </span><i><em class=3D"GFGEditorTheme__t=
extItalic">true</em></i><span>). It focuses on binary variables and logic o=
perations such as AND, OR, and NOT.</span></p><ul><li value=3D"1"><span>Boo=
lean Algebra provides a formal way to represent and manipulate logical stat=
ements and binary operations. </span></li><li value=3D"2"><span>It is the m=
athematical foundation of digital electronics, computer logic, and programm=
ing conditions.</span></li></ul><h2 id=3D"boolean-algebra-operations" style=
=3D"text-align:left"><span>Logical Operations</span></h2><p dir=3D"ltr"><sp=
an>Various operations are used in Boolean algebra, but the basic operations=
 that form the base of Boolean Algebra are:</span></p><blockquote><p dir=3D=
"ltr"><b><strong>=E2=80=A2 Negation </strong></b><span>or NOT Operation</sp=
an><br><b><strong>=E2=80=A2 Conjunction </strong></b><span>or AND Operation=
</span><br><b><strong>=E2=80=A2 Disjunction </strong></b><span>or OR Operat=
ion</span></p></blockquote><figure class=3D"image"><img src=3D"https://medi=
a.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20240507171330/Boolean-Algebra-Opera=
tions-660.png" alt=3D"Boolean-Algebra-Operations" width=3D"660" height=3D"4=
72"><figcaption>3 Basic Boolean Operations</figcaption></figure><p dir=3D"l=
tr"><span>These operations have their oymbols and precedence ,and the table=
 added below shows the ssymbolsand the precedence of these operators.</span=
></p><table><thead><tr><th><p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"text-align: center;"><sp=
